🎯 Django Channels Learning Roadmap (Professional Level)
Phase 1: Core Concepts & Setup (1–2 days)

Goal: Understand the foundation.

Topics to Learn:

ASGI vs WSGI – why Channels uses ASGI

Consumers:

WebsocketConsumer (sync)

AsyncWebsocketConsumer (async)

WebSocket lifecycle:

connect()

receive()

disconnect()

Scope & self.scope:

Access user, session, path, etc.

Channel layer basics:

How Channels uses Redis to route messages

Channel vs Group vs Room

Routing:

How routing.py connects WebSocket paths to consumers

Exercise:

Build a simple WebSocket echo server:

Browser sends a message → server sends it back



Phase 2: Groups & Broadcasting (2–3 days)

Goal: Handle multiple users in a room.

Topics:

group_add, group_discard, group_send

Rooms:

Map business room concept → Channels group

Multiple connections per user:

Tabs, devices

Redis channel routing

Exercise:

Build a chat room:

Multiple users connected → messages broadcast to all in that room

Phase 3: Persistence & DB Integration (3–5 days)

Goal: Save messages and fetch old ones.

Topics:

Database in async consumers:

Use database_sync_to_async

Saving messages to DB for offline access

Fetching old messages on connect()

Serializers integration (like DRF)

Authentication in WebSocket:

AuthMiddlewareStack or JWT

Signals + Channels (trigger WS notifications from DB events)

Exercise:

Chat app with persistence:

Messages saved to DB

Load last 50 messages on page load

Deliver new messages live

Phase 4: Advanced Real-Time Features (4–5 days)

Goal: Production-ready real-time features.

Topics:

Online/offline presence tracking

Typing indicators & read receipts

Private messages with permissions

Handling disconnects & reconnects

Scaling Channels:

Multiple workers

Redis for cross-worker communication

Exercise:

Chat app enhancements:

Show online users

Typing indicators

Only authorized users can join room

Phase 5: Production & Deployment (2–3 days)

Goal: Make your Channels app production-ready.

Topics:

Auth & permission checks

Rate limiting & security

Handling bad/disconnect events

Deployment:

Daphne/Uvicorn + Nginx

Dockerize Channels

Multiple workers + Redis

Monitoring with Flower or Prometheus

Exercise:

Deploy chat app to test server

Test multiple workers, Redis, and persistent messages

Phase 6: Optional Advanced Topics (2–3 days)

Presence for large-scale apps (Redis pub/sub or external store)

Offline message delivery (queue messages for offline users)

WebRTC signaling with Channels (for audio/video calls)

Performance optimization (async DB queries, caching, reduce Redis calls)

🔹 Suggested Daily Routine

2–3 hours/day focused on coding and experimenting

Build projects as you learn

Total time to reach professional level: ~4–6 weeks